76561198052187998,Not Recommended,433280,20726348,"Posted: 24 January, 2016",all,Aelies von Saladir,"I love this game and had played it for 1000+ hours in my youth. However, I really can't recommend this version of the game at all as it includes fan patches that not only fix the bugs but also change the gameplay drastically.Scroll down for what I said when I thought this was the official version and what I'd restore along with a recommendation if it is reverted to the official version.It's like having a reunion with a long lost childhood friend, only to find that, during our long separation, aliens have abducted him, experimented on him and gave him an extensive modification before letting him go. While these modifications are, according to the aliens, improvement, the person is no longer your childhood friend but a total stranger wearing your friend's face.So, if you've played the official version and is planning on getting this for nostalgia's sake you should at least find out what the fan patch changes and decide whether or not you could live with it.Original ReviewNote that I'll be approaching this game from a(n extremely) nostalgic point of view.The moment I saw this game on steam, the first thing I was checking if my eyes were deceiving me.And when I could confirm that it is really here, I bought it without any hesitation.This game literally is my childhood. While it is certainly not the first RTS I've ever played, It's certainly what instill the love of the genre in me.On to the game itself, there are two features which, to me, give this game the charm that even modern RTSs couldn't match; the hero system and the races.There are 16 races in this game and all of them are almost completely unique (there're a few units that turn up in more than one races, like peasants, the builder unit for both Knights and Empire). While this introduce some balance problems (like how the Orcs have limited anti air capabilities while the Demons have air superiority, which will put Orcs at a disadvantage should the two races are put to fight each other), the variety results in an almost endless strategic possibilities and is like a playground for a child's imagination. Even as an adult, I still sometimes think back to the days before I lost the disc and imagine how the races interact with another. There're few games that let war elephants duke it out with a freaking T-rex (yes, there are T-rexes in this game, and it's almost worth buying just for them alone).And now for the hero system, instead of playing separate battles and begin anew every time, you create persistent heroes (which you can choose from all the sixteen races and twenty eight classes, in an almost RPG-like system) and have them, and their retinue of hand-picked troops, leading the battles. While this, again, creates balance problems (as a level 50+ hero could probably stemroll an entire base lead by a level 1 hero, even though there are temporary heroes and no heroes mode designed to avoid that), it also leads to a very satisfyinng gameplay as you build your hero up, finding new gears and gaining new abilities and more overpowered retinues. The system let you immerse yourself in your hero's journey and exercise your imagination. Even after many, many year, I still remember fondly my favourite hero, a Ssrathi (basically half man, half snake) Paladin, equally skilled in close combat and healing Magic, bodyguarded by a T-rex, a Minotaur King (who is as tall as the T-rex), a Knight Lord, a High Elven Moonguard and a white dragon. Isn't that awesome? That's the kind of experience this game gives. And of course, ther're so many other builds out there that could satisfy basically any idea.The game isn't without its flaw and even its huge fan like me acknowledges that. It seems to focus on diversity of builds and strategies rather than balance, the point I've already brought up (twice). And the graphic is pretty old even in 2004 (when it came out) and is completely outdated in 2016. Still, if you can get past that and you like RTSs, RPGs or a great mix of both, I believe this game will satisfy your need and your imagination quite nicely."
