,Recommended,433280,30524153,Posted: 15 March,all,Aron,"From the series I have only played Warlords Battlecry III, but it is a big favorite of mine nevertheless.The RTS SideAs you probably know, Warlords Battlecry III is a Real Time Strategy (RTS) game, just like the Age Of ___ games or Starcraft, Warcraft. What makes it unique is its large amount of races to play with - 16 to be exact - from Elves to Dwarves, Minotaurs, Daemons, different reptiles, etc.There is a conversion mechanism for buildings - some units can perform aconvertaction which will turn nearby buildings to the player's side. This is how the resources (Gold, Crystal, Metal and Stone) are handled - you have to convert the mines which will produce for you.The RPG SideA neat feature in Warlords Battlecry III is that the player has their own hero, a superunit who stays with the player between battles and gains experience to level up. There is a huge list of classes to pick for the Hero, such as Merchant, Dragonslayer, Pyromancer, etc.Heroes can learn spells in many different spell schools - Alchemy, Chaos, Divination, Nature, Poison, Necromancy, and of course the basic ones like Fire or Ice. Additionally, Heroes have an Equipment and Inventory system - with Set items to collect too.The Gameplay SideWarlords Battlecry III offers a Campaign Mode to take on with a unique storyline.The player can take their hero to independent battles in Skirmish Mode and play on either randomly generated or manual maps with up to 5 AIs.Lastly, there is an Editor in which the player can assemble their own maps.Last WordsRTS + RPG, perfectly falls in a good old game category. Definitely recommended."
76561198039166993,Recommended,433280,20759510,"Posted: 25 January, 2016",all,҉҈F҈҉A҈҉G҈҉G҈҉O҈҉T҉,"This is one of my favorite games of all time. Even today Warlords Battlecry 3 has a lot to offer to the real time strategy genre, even if at moments the implementation is a little sloppy. It has a ton of races to choose from, and a persistent hero unit you can bring from game to game as well as units you can level up and put into your retinue to also bring from game to game(if they die they are dead forever though, unlike your hero unless you choose ironman mode). The graphics haven't aged very well but it is still an extremely fun experience for anyone who has not played it before.Edit: I have played this game for hundreds of hours during my childhood, i have played much longer then 30 minutes."
