76561198053058189,Recommended,433280,20757423,"Posted: 25 January, 2016",all,Chronie,"Rating systemThere are 5 grades of quality for me5 Good the people have actually taken their time to do things well4 Cheap meaning lacking in some areas that could have major improvements3 Fast referring to a buggy or poorly run game2 Half-arsed made for the sole purpose of maximizing profits, business that developed it got taken advantage of or some mechanics/strategies ruined1 Garbage unplayableWith games there can be issues to reduce the quality of the game or the story that change the overall experience.Warlords of Battlecry 3Gameplay4	Many people take the easiest route the warrior and rush through the gameReplayability5	Most classes offer a significantly different method of playVersion2	Changes to the game are a matter of opinion made by fansOverall 	3.67 out of 5 averageIf switched back to official versionOverall	4.5 out of 5 averageUnofficial patch has changed the game too much from what it was and there is a way to remove those changes from the game in the forums as it falls so far from the original game which many of the good reviews are about. These changes have re-balanced many of the units and heroes to suit more of an arena style of play. For an actual change log you would have go to the site in order to see the full list.This is one of the best RTS games of it's time and although the graphics have aged quite a bit it allowed you to greatly customise your hero and allow many different tactics to be used with each team. There are a total of 16 different races (some better against others) and a large game world to explore in a series of skirmishes or short missions. The major focus was on the hero and it's development in the game which race or races would it lead into battle, what are it's skills going to be and what equipment their was. While it is possible to play the game without heroes there was also no limit to their development. Races are not balanced or set to a specific play style you will need to use different tactics to stand a chance when faced with a racial mismatch but the game is almost always win-able.The unofficial patch heroes for example have had many of their abilities changed to empower warrior type characters. New spell sets have been added and mage abilities changed to better suit the method of the modders. Summons are the most noticeable difference as you now have a limited duration on units that would likely have died due to a lack of healing from your team. The magic system in short has been altered to prevent some tactics and give others a chance if they unload all their spells at once a much harder system for people to learn.Most units from what I can remember from the original have had at least one value changed from cost to massive increases to health, armor or damage. This isn't a small change either with some of them getting double health or similar changes. The result is an over developed patched version of a game that was good by itself.Unfortunately it seems to be a case of if it ain't broken why fix it. The game is less friendly than the original for new people and many older players want their classic game back. You could call this Warlords Battlecry 4 for all the changes they have done but they aren't good ones. Play the version you want and try the 1.30B patch in compadibility mode before you judge the game."
